

Fetch API
=========

The Fetch API is a modern built_in browser feature for making network requests. 
It provides a simple and powerful way to fetch data from APIs.



//example 

fetch(url)
 .then(response => response.json())
 .then(data => {
     //Process the data
     console.log(data)
 })
 .catch(error => {
     //Handle the error
     console.error(error)
 })



 Async/await 
 ===========

 You can use the async/await syntax in combination with the fetch API to make the code readable and handle asynchronous operations.
 

 async function fetchData() {
     try {
          const response = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data')
          const data = await response.json();
     }
     catch(error) {

          //handle the error
          console.error(error)
     }
 }
 
 
 useEffect(() => {
    fetch("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts")
    .then((response) => {
      if(!response.ok){
        throw new Error("Network response was not ok")
      }
      return response.json();
    })
    .then((data) => {
      setData(data);
      setLoading(false);
    })
    .catch((error) => {
      setError(error);
      setLoading(false);
    })
  },[])



